title: Celestial Space
description: Six ambient tracks ranging from celestial & calm to scary & ominous.
longDescription:
Preview: youtube.com/watch?v=CjmaC6oBllI

Six ambient tracks, that range from celestial and calm to scary and ominous.
Although titled "Space", these suit multiple styles, whether that's down to earth fantasy/mystery, or a distant world of your crazy imagination.

Tracks:
1. Celestial Orbit - a peaceful, warm moment. Imagine a space ship slowly flowing above a planet or a view to milky-way.
2. Abandoned Infinity - Desolated view to an abandoned landscape or perhaps an asteroid field filled with wreckage of war. An ominous and intriguing track suitable for both outdoor and indoor exploration.
3. Dead Station - Inspired by 'Aliens' by the great James Horner (RIP). Imagine approaching/entering an abandoned space station and getting that familiar feeling; “There’s something out there, something in the shadows, and it’s not good”. Dark, ominous and even a bit chaotic underscore when one’s needed.
4. Solitude - It's great to be left alone to die in space, isn't it? End of all things? Or perhaps peace? Calm and gentle piece with a resolute, hopeful feeling.
5. Aliens on a Space Station - Relative to 'Dead Station'. Slowly pulsating, dark and ominous, and a bit chaotic track.
6. Celestial Rising - Peaceful and a bit mysterious ending to all things.
